Web Storage:

HTML5 Web Storage allows us to store information locally on user's computers.
Works like Cookies, but it is faster and better
The information stored in web storage is not sent to the server.
The information stored in cookies is always sent to the web server with every request.
In a cookie you can store data of approximately 4kB
In web storage, you can store up to 5MB

Two types of web storage:
    Local storage uses the localstorage object
    stores data for your website on a permanent basis

    Session storage uses the session storage object
    store the data for your website on a temporary basis
    The data disappears when session ends or browser windows or tab gets closed.

Cookies
    A small text file to store a small amount of information around 4kb on the user's computer
    
